s=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        How do I use the hair cover-up powder?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>Simply tap the sponge applicator onto the desired area and blend gently. It instantly fills gaps and creates a fuller, natural look in seconds.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        Will it look natural on my hair or brows?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>Yes! The powder is designed to blend seamlessly with your natural hair color, giving you a soft, realistic finish without harsh lines.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        How long does it last?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>It provides long-lasting coverage throughout the day and stays in place until you wash it off.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        Is it easy to carry and use on the go?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>Absolutely. Its compact design makes it perfect for quick touch-ups anytime, anywhere.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"faq-item\">\n      <button class=\"faq-question\" onclick=\"toggleFaq(this)\">\n        Is it suitable for all hair types?\n        <span class=\"faq-icon\">+</span>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n        <p>Yes, it works for all hair types and textures, helping you achieve a fuller, more defined look effortlessly.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n  function toggleFaq(btn) {\n    const answer = btn.nextElementSibling;\n    const isOpen = btn.classList.contains('open');\n\n    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question').forEach(q => q.classList.remove('open'));\n    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer').forEach(a => a.classList.remove('open'));\n\n    if (!isOpen) {\n      btn.classList.add('open');\n      answer.classList.add('open');\n    }\n  }\n</script>",
